<HEADLINE> Clippers Give Up Vrankovic Rights </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- The Los Angeles Clippers renounced their  
rights to free agent center Stojko Vrankovic on Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Vrankovic, 35, played in two games for the Clippers last season,  
scoring two points and grabbing six rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
	The 7-foot-2 Vrankovic came to the Clippers from Minnesota on  
June 25, 1997, in a trade for center Stanley Roberts. Vrankovic 
played in 65 games for the Clippers in 1997-98, averaging 3.0 
points and 4.0 rebounds. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
