<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Suspect Killed in Wall St. Shootout </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- A suspected bank robber who returned to the  
scene of a June heist was shot and killed after police chased him 
through the Wall Street financial district during a bustling noon 
hour. 
</P>
<P>
	Officers fired about 35 bullets but were uncertain whether the  
man fired his gun, said Assistant Chief William Taylor. A passerby 
was wounded. 
</P>
<P>
	``It was a crazy scene,'' said Anthony Frangello, who works in  
the Wall Street area where Monday's chase began. ``People were 
falling, trampling over each other trying to get out of the way.'' 
</P>
<P>
	A teller at an HSBC Bank branch just blocks from the New York  
Stock Exchange recognized a man wearing a business suit in the bank 
as the same person who held her up in June. A security officer 
called police. 
</P>
<P>
	When an officer confronted the man inside the bank, he pulled  
out a gun and refused to put it down, so officers began firing, 
Taylor said. 
</P>
<P>
	The man, whose name was not released, was hit by a bullet, but  
he ran outside and into crowds of office workers on their lunch 
breaks. 
</P>
<P>
	``Blood flew everywhere, it was on the sidewalk in splatters,''  
said Donald Littlejohn, who works as a clown at a nearby park. ``It 
was like they were shooting a movie.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The man ducked behind cars and around corners as police chased  
and fired at him. He fell about a block from the bank and was later 
declared dead. Police did not know how many times the man had been 
hit. 
</P>
<P>
	``The perpetrator had a loaded gun,'' Taylor said. ``We're not  
sure in the commotion whether or not his gun was fired.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Littlejohn said he saw the man shoot several times. ``I saw the  
guy turn around, fire about five to seven rounds.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Rita Rosenberg, 59, of Cliffside Park, N.J., was shot in the  
buttocks and was taken to Bellevue Hospital Center, where she was 
in stable condition. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
