<HEADLINE> 'Sixth Sense' Tops 'Witch', 'Bride' / Box Office  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Bruce Willis' ``The Sixth Sense'' won the  
fright-film fight, beating out ``The Blair Witch Project'' to top 
the weekend box office with a shocking $26.7 million. 
</P>
<P>
	Low-budget horror hit ``The Blair Witch Project'' stayed in  
second place with $24.3 million. Last week's top movie, the Julia 
Roberts-Richard Gere comedy ``Runaway Bride,'' fell to third with 
$20.8 million. 
</P>
<P>
	``The Thomas Crown Affair,'' a Pierce Brosnan-Rene Russo remake  
