<HEADLINE> Tokyo Stocks Down / Japanese Stocks  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TOKYO (AP) -- The dollar edged lower against the yen early  
Wednesday, while Japanese stocks fell moderately following an 
overnight decline on Wall Street. 
</P>
<P>
	The dollar bought 114.82 yen in early trading, down 0.06 yen  
from late Tuesday in Tokyo but marginally above its late New York 
level of 114.81 yen. 
</P>
<P>
	The benchmark 225-issue Nikkei Stock Average shed 83.87 points,  
or 0.49 percent, to 17,118.22 in the first 30 minutes of trading. 
On Tuesday, the average closed up 11.64 points, or 0.07 percent. 
</P>
<P>
	In currency dealings, the dollar slipped after some  
institutional investors adjusted positions in subdued trading amid 
Japan's summer holiday season. 
</P>
<P>
	In other currencies, the euro was traded at 122.66 yen, down  
from 123.30 late Tuesday in Tokyo. 
</P>
<P>
	On the stock market, prices started moderately weaker in already  
quiet trading as many participants retreated to the sidelines for 
Japan's summer ``Obon'' holidays. 
</P>
<P>
	In New York, the Dow Jones industrial average fell 52.55 points  
to close at 10,655.15 at Tuesday's close. The technology-rich 
Nasdaq composite index also fell 28.87 points to 2,490.11. 
</P>
<P>
	The broader Tokyo Stock Price Index of all issues listed on the  
first section was down 8.27 points, or 0.58 percent, to 1,415.98. 
The TOPIX closed down 0.28 point, or 0.02 percent, the day before. 
</P>
<P>
	The yield on the benchmark 10-year Japanese government bond fell  
to 1.8800 percent from Tuesday's finish of 1.8950 percent, driving 
its price up to 99.32 yen from 99.19 yen. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
