<HEADLINE> Broncos' Mobley Gets Probation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CASTLE ROCK, Colo. (AP) -- Denver Broncos linebacker John Mobley  
will have to do 24 hours of community service and undergo an 
alcohol evaluation following his car accident last month. 
</P>
<P>
	Mobley pleaded guilty to driving while ability impaired,  
careless driving, and driving without a valid driver's license 
during a hearing in Douglas County Court on Tuesday, said Michael 
Knight, spokesman for the district attorney's office. 
</P>
<P>
	Mobley originally faced more serious charges, but Knight said  
Mobley's plea agreement is not unusual. 
</P>
<P>
	``He didn't receive anything special,'' Knight said.  
</P>
<P>
	Mobley flipped his 1997 Jaguar on June 23 in suburban Douglas  
County, about 30 miles southeast of Denver. He initially was 
charged with driving under the influence, driving carelessly and 
driving under a suspended license. 
</P>
<P>
	He had a blood-alcohol level of 0.139 at the time. A driver in  
Colorado is presumed drunk at 0.10. 
</P>
<P>
	Under his agreement with the court, Mobley will be on probation  
for one year and must perform the 24 hours' community service, half 
of that for Mothers Against Drunk Driving. 
</P>
<P>
	He must also pay $553 in fines and costs and undergo an alcohol  
evaluation and any recommended treatment. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
