<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> European Stocks Close Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- European stocks closed higher Monday, buoyed by  
rising oil prices and gains in telecommunications. 
</P>
<P>
	Elf Aquitaine and TotalFina led the rises in energy shares on  
speculation that the two companies are preparing to merge. 
</P>
<P>
	Meanwhile, Deutsche Telekom rose after the company said it's not  
expecting the acquisition of British mobile telephone operator 
One2One to hurt its dividend. 
</P>
<P>
	The Dow Jones Stoxx Index of 592 European companies rose 2.66  
points, or 0.9 percent, to close at 296.34, while the Dow Jones 
Euro Stoxx Index, which tracks 297 companies in countries that 
joined the single currency, closed up 4.82 points at 308.57. 
</P>
<P>
	Energy stocks were the best performers, with a gain of 2.2  
percent, as oil prices weren't affected by the latest developments 
in Russia. 
</P>
<P>
	Trading in Russian shares was halted for a half-hour at the open  
after the key index slid 11 percent following President Boris 
Yeltsin's firing of his fourth prime minister in less than 18 
months. However, the news had little impact on European markets. 
</P>
<P>
	In London, shares of BP Amoco, the most heavily weighted stock  
in the Dow Jones Stoxx Index, closed up 7 pence at 1,241 pence. In 
Paris, shares of Elf Aquitaine rose 4 percent, while TotalFina rose 
4.1 percent. 
</P>
<P>
	The Dow Jones Euro Stoxx 50 Index rose 60.11 points to close at  
3,585.58, while the DJ Stoxx 50 Index closed up 33.88 points at 
3,550.41. 
</P>
<P>
	In domestic markets, the Paris CAC-40 index closed up 1.6  
percent to 4,292.90, Frankfurt's Xetra DAX index rose 1.5 percent 
to 5,087.30, Amsterdam's AEX index rose 1.6 percent to 543.39 and 
Milan's MIBtel index rose 1.6 percent to 32,250. London's FTSE 100 
index gained 0.1 percent to 6,126.40 
</P>
<P>
	Russian shares recouped most of their losses, with the Russian  
Trading System index falling 1.4 percent to end at 101.72. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
