<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Root-Lowell Recalls Sprayers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Root-Lowell Manufacturing Co. is recalling  
90,000 home and garden sprayers with pumps that can spontaneously 
shoot out of the sprayers and cause injuries, the Consumer Product 
Safety Commission said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	The recall only affects the one-gallon, pump-style sprayers made  
by the company, which is based in Lowell, Mich. The sprayers, with 
white containers and black pump assemblies, are typically used with 
liquid fertilizer or cleaning agents. They were sold from January 
through July. 
</P>
<P>
	Root-Lowell received three reports of the pump assembly ejecting  
from the sprayer without warning, causing three injuries, including 
lacerations, facial injuries and chest bruising. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
