<HEADLINE> Miller, Langdon Sign With Cavaliers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CLEVELAND (AP) -- Guards Andre Miller and Trajan Langdon, the  
Cleveland Cavaliers' top two draft picks, signed contracts with the 
team Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Miller will earn approximately $5.4 million over the first three  
years of his contract, with the Cavaliers holding the option for a 
fourth year at $2.1 million. 
</P>
<P>
	The 6-foot-2, 200-pound point guard from Utah was the Cavs'  
first pick and No. 8 overall. He averaged 15.8 points last season 
and led the Utes in scoring, assists and steals. With him running 
the point, the Utes went 114-20 the past four seasons. 
</P>
<P>
	Langdon averaged 14.5 points in 136 games at Duke. Last season,  
the 6-foot-3 guard averaged 17.3 points and made 44 percent of his 
3-point attempts. 
</P>
<P>
	Langdon will earn approximately $4.5 million over his first  
three years, with the Cavs holding the option for a fourth year at 
$2.1 million. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
