<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> 16 Hurt in Airport Shuttle Bus Crash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- An airport shuttle bus collided with more  
than a dozen vehicles Tuesday at a major intersection bordering Los 
Angeles International Airport, injuring 16 people and tangling 
morning airport traffic for hours. 
</P>
<P>
	Nine people were hospitalized and six people suffered what  
appeared to be serious injuries, Fire Department spokesman Jim 
Wells said. Seven people were treated at the scene. 
</P>
<P>
	There were no passengers on the Alamo rental car shuttle, said  
Oscar Suris, spokesman for Fort Lauderdale, Fla.-based AutoNation 
Inc., parent of Alamo. The driver wasn't hurt. 
</P>
<P>
	The bus crashed into 16 vehicles, including a car that was  
crushed at a Texaco gas station, narrowly missing pumps. 
</P>
<P>
	Alamo spokeswoman Cheryl Budd said the brakes failed on the bus.  
</P>
<P>
	The crash investigation closed the intersection for hours,  
snarling traffic for blocks and delaying airport-bound travelers. 


  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
