<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Mountain Bike Forks Recalled </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- A Taiwanese company, Hsin Lung Accessory, is  
recalling about 1,400 bicycle suspension forks installed on Huffy 
Company mountain bikes, which can break and cause serious injuries, 
the Consumer Product Safety Commission said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	The suspension forks, which are black and have ``Zoom'' written  
on them, were used for the Huffy Bicycle Company's ``Verdict'' 
mountain bikes. The bikes in question were sold in the United 
States from January to June for about $200. 
</P>
<P>
	Hsin Lung Accessory has received reports of three incidents when  
the forks broke, causing serious injuries to riders. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
