<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-10 02:20:14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Shatner's Wife Found Dead in Pool </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- The wife of actor William Shatner was found  
dead Monday evening in the deep end of the swimming pool at his 
home, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
	The 40-year-old woman was pronounced dead at the scene. Her name  
was not immediately released. 
</P>
<P>
	Officer Barbara Carranza, Los Angeles Police department  
spokeswoman, said Shatner arrived home around 10 p.m. and found his 
wife in the water. 
</P>
<P>
	``He pulled his wife from the pool, called 911 and was  
instructed to begin CPR, which he did,'' she said. 
</P>
<P>
	By the time firefighters arrived, the caller had apparently  
pulled the woman out of the water. 
</P>
<P>
	``Sadly, she was beyond our help,'' Los Angeles Fire Department  
spokesman Brian Humphrey said. 
</P>
<P>
	Shatner's manager, Larry Thompson, said he hadn't heard about a  
death there. ``I know nothing about this,'' Thompson said. 
</P>
<P>
	Shatner is best known as Capt. James T. Kirk on the science  
fiction television show ``Star Trek.'' He also appeared in several 
``Star Trek'' movies and the 1980s television police drama ``T.J. 
Hooker.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Carranza said the cause of death will be determined by the Los  
Angeles coroner's office. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
