<HEADLINE> Big Movers in the Stock Market  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks that moved substantially or traded  
heavily Tuesday on the New York Stock Exchange and Nasdaq Stock 
Market. 

</P>
<P>
                               *NYSE    	

</P>
<P>
 *Lucent Technologies Inc., down 2 at 61 5/8  
</P>
<P>
 *International Network Services Inc., up 3 at 50 7/16 on the Nasdaq 
</P>
<P>
	Lucent is buying INS for about $3.7 billion, bolstering Lucent's  
push into the fast-growing arena of advising corporations on 
setting up high-speed data networks. Lucent has made several recent 
acquisitions of computer networking companies. 

</P>
<P>
 *Hillenbrand Industries, down 9 7/16 at 33 1/16    	
</P>
<P>
	The company, a maker of caskets, said its third-quarter profits  
from continuing operations will miss Wall Street estimates of 64 
cents per share by 25 cents to 39 cents per share. Hillenbrand 
cited an unexpected Medicare charge and lower than expected sales 
at certain units. 

</P>
