</P>
<P>
 *Gold Banc Corporation Inc., down 1/16 at 11 7/16 
</P>
<P>
	Union Bankshares, a Denver-based bank, will be acquired by Gold  
Banc in a $65 million stock swap. The deal is the largest 
acquisition ever for Gold Banc, a rapidly growing bank based in 
Leawood, Kan. 

</P>
<P>
 *Zonagen Inc., down 2 3/8 at 4 15/16    	
</P>
<P>
	The Food and Drug Administration banned further human trials of  
Zonagen's impotence-treatment drug, Vasomax. Tests performed on 
rats showed that male rats taking the drug's active compound, 
phentolamine, developed more brown fat tissue. Schering-Plough, 
Zonagen's licensee, will be allowed to continue a 12-week study of 
Vasomax. 

</P>
<P>
 *Healtheon Corp., down 7 3/16 at 31 3/4    	
</P>
<P>
	Traders suggested the expiration of Healtheon's post-IPO  
prohibition on stock sales by insiders spurred selling by 
executives of Healtheon. Many companies making initial public 
offerings ban employees or other insiders from selling their shares 
before a certain date. 


  	   	
