<HEADLINE> Interest Rates Rise for T-Bills / T-Bills  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Yields on five-year Treasury notes rose in  
Tuesday's auction to the highest level in almost two years. 
</P>
<P>
	The yield was 6.014 percent, up from 5.367 percent at the last  
auction on May 11. It was the highest rate since five-year notes 
sold for 6.253 percent on August 27, 1997. 
</P>
<P>
	The notes will carry a coupon interest rate of 6 percent with  
each $10,000 in face value selling for $9,994.00. 
</P>
<P>
	A total of $15 billion in notes were sold out of bids totaling  
$27.7 billion. 
  	   	
</P>
