<HEADLINE> State Department Economist Dies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Sandra B. O'Leary, a top State Department  
economic official in both Republican and Democratic 
administrations, has died of cancer. She was 50. 
</P>
<P>
	O'Leary, who served as an economic advisor to Secretaries of  
State George Shultz and James Baker before eventually becoming a 
deputy assistant secretary of state for economic policy in the 
Clinton administration, died Monday at her home in McLean, Va. 
</P>
<P>
	Most recently, she worked as a professor at the Foreign Service  
Institute and the National Defense University. 
</P>
<P>
	She is survived by her husband, James O'Leary, two daughters,  
Glynis and Abigail; her father, Boniface Brazaitis, and a sister, 
C.B. Lovell, both of Columbia, Md. 
  	   	
</P>
