facilities and technical superiority. 
</P>
<P>
	``Everybody still has a chance,'' said Beckenbauer, the captain  
of the 1974 German team that won the World Cup title at home and 
coach of the 1990 side that captured the title in Italy. ``Our job 
is now to convince everybody that Germany is the best place for the 
World Cup.'' 
</P>
<P>
	On Monday, South Africa made en emotional appeal to host the  
continent's first World Cup, evoking the nation's troubled, 
turbulent past. The nation insists it has the necessary 
infrastructure to host a World Cup, and spent considerable time 
