<HEADLINE> Tokyo Stocks Rise / Japanese Stocks  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TOKYO (AP) -- The dollar edged lower against the yen Wednesday  
morning in thin trading. Tokyo share prices rose moderately after a 
weak start. 
</P>
<P>
	The dollar bought 114.79 yen at late morning, down 0.09 yen from  
late Tuesday in Tokyo and also marginally below its late New York 
level of 114.81 yen. 
</P>
<P>
	The benchmark 225-issue Nikkei Stock Average gained 71.90  
points, or 0.42 percent, to 17,273.99 at the end of the morning 
session. On Tuesday, the average closed up 11.64 points, or 0.07 
percent. 
</P>
<P>
	In currency dealings, the dollar inched down after Japanese  
institutional investors adjusted positions in subdued trading amid 
Japan's summer holiday season. 
</P>
<P>
	In other currencies, the euro was traded at 122.95 yen, down  
from 123.30 late Tuesday in Tokyo. 
</P>
<P>
	On the Tokyo stock market, prices opened moderately lower in  
already quiet trading as many participants retreated to the 
sidelines as Japan headed into the peak of the summer holiday. 
</P>
<P>
	But the Tokyo market moved into positive territory by  
mid-morning as buying of futures bolstered sentiment among players, 
traders said. 
</P>
<P>
	In New York, the Dow Jones industrial average fell 52.55 points  
to close at 10,655.15 on Tuesday. The technology-rich Nasdaq 
composite index also fell 28.87 points to 2,490.11. 
</P>
<P>
	The broader Tokyo Stock Price Index of all issues listed on the  
first section was up 1.53 points, or 0.11 percent, to 1,425.78. The 
TOPIX closed down 0.28 point, or 0.02 percent, the day before. 
</P>
<P>
	The yield on the benchmark 10-year Japanese government bond rose  
to 1.9100 percent from Tuesday's finish of 1.8950 percent, driving 
its price down to 99.06 yen from 99.19 yen. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
