<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Shock 84, Sparks 59 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	INGLEWOOD, Calif. (AP) -- Detroit reserve Dominique Canty scored  
13 second-half points as the Shock beat the Los Angeles Sparks 
84-59 Monday night. 
</P>
<P>
	Canty finished with 18 points, Jennifer Azzi added 15 and  
recently-acquired Wendy Palmer scored 15 and had 12 rebounds as 
Detroit won for just the second time in eight games. 
</P>
<P>
	Detroit (12-14) led 42-26 at halftime and opened the second half  
with six unanswered points. The Sparks' 9-0 run cut the deficit to 
51-42 with 13:02 left, but the Shock put the game away with 11 
unanswered points for a 64-44 advantage with 9:11 remaining. 
</P>
<P>
	DeLisha Milton had 16 and La'Keshia Frett 12 for Los Angeles  
(17-8). The loss was the Sparks' worst of the season and the second 
in their last three games following a franchise-record tying 
six-game winning streak. 
</P>
<P>
	Los Angeles missed 14 of its first 15 shots and trailed 19-2  
6:28 into the game. Palmer, obtained in a July 29 trade with Utah, 
scored seven points during Detroit's 13-0 run which gave it the 
17-point advantage. A 6-0 spurt gave the Shock its biggest 
first-half lead, 29-9, 8:40 before halftime. 
</P>
<P>
	The victory moved the Shock two games ahead of Orlando (10-16)  
in the race for the Eastern Conference's final playoff berth. Both 
teams have six games remaining. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
