<HEADLINE> eBay Hires Tech Executive </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SAN JOSE, Calif. (AP) -- Online auction company eBay Inc. has  
hired Gateway Inc.'s chief information officer to be its new 
technology executive and help end a series of debilitating computer 
failures. 
</P>
<P>
	Maynard Webb, 43, will lead eBay's other recently hired  
technology executives: chief technology officer Mark Ryan, 
previously of IBM, and chief information officer Bob Quinn, 
formerly of Sun Microsystems. 
</P>
<P>
	Shares of eBay jumped more than 12 percent, or $9.62 1/2, on the  
news to close at $89.25 on the Nasdaq Stock Market. 
</P>
<P>
	At Gateway, Webb worked on expanding the e-commerce operations  
of the nation's No. 2 computer maker. As eBay Technologies 
president, Webb will report directly to eBay CEO Meg Whitman. 
</P>
<P>
	``We are confident that he possesses the vision and hands-on  
experience to help ensure eBay's site stability moving forward and 
to help scale eBay's system for the future,'' Whitman said in 
announcing his appointment on Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	EBay's site went down again Sunday for nearly three hours when  
credit card processing failed. The site crashed for nearly 10 hours 
Friday and for nearly 24 consecutive hours in June. 


  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
