<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Mesaba Attendants Vote on Union </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MINNEAPOLIS (AP) -- Ballots were mailed to Mesaba Airlines' 500  
flight attendants Tuesday for a vote on whether they want the 
Association of Flight Attendants to act as their bargaining 
representative. 
</P>
<P>
	The ballots will be counted Sept. 8.  
</P>
<P>
	Minneapolis-based Mesaba operates as a Northwest Airlink  
affiliate out of Northwest Airlines hubs in Minneapolis-St. Paul, 
Detroit and Memphis, Tenn. The carrier serves 100 cities in 25 
states and Canada. 
</P>
<P>
	The AFA is the world's largest flight attendant union,  
representing 46,000 flight attendants at 25 airlines. 
</P>
<P>
	Two work groups at Mesaba are unionized. The pilots are  
represented by the Air Line Pilots Association and the mechanics by 
the Airline Mechanics Professional Fraternal Association. 

  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
