<HEADLINE> Arizona's Anderson Hit by Line Drive </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CHICAGO (AP) -- Arizona Diamondbacks pitcher Brian Anderson left  
Tuesday's game against the Chicago Cubs in the second inning when 
he was hit in the left arm by a line drive off the bat of Henry 
Rodriguez. 
</P>
<P>
	Anderson had little time to react to the hard-hit ball, which  
appeared to strike him on the left arm above the elbow. His glove 
fell off and Anderson never tried for the ball, which landed near 
the mound, but instead held his left arm. 
</P>
<P>
	Anderson, who was relieved by Erik Sabel, allowed one run and  
three hits in one-plus innings. It was his 14 start and 22nd 
appearance this year. 
