<HEADLINE> Cops: Calif. Man Kills 4, Kidnaps Ex </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ROSEMEAD, Calif. (AP) -- A woman was found alive today after  
being kidnapped from a house where four people were killed and two 
others were wounded, allegedly by the woman's ex-boyfriend. 
</P>
<P>
	The ex-boyfriend apparently was upset at the failure of their  
relationship, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
	The 40-year-old woman was found early today after being  
released, and she was taken to a hospital for examination, Los 
Angeles County sheriff's Deputy Margarita Velazquez said. 
</P>
<P>
	Investigators were still looking for Evelio Rivera Zacarias, 42,  
who had fled with the woman Monday in a pickup, Deputy Carrie 
Stuart said 
</P>
<P>
	Officials did not immediately say how or where the woman was  
released. 
</P>
<P>
	The shooting happened about 8:30 p.m. Monday in a home in  
Rosemead, northeast of downtown Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
	``We heard multiple gunshots, about four, and then two minutes  
later another four or five more,'' said David Miranda, who lives 
next door. ``It was not a drive-by. Someone was emptying their 
gun.'' 
</P>
<P>
	None of the victims' names were released but the woman's current  
boyfriend was among the dead, Stuart said. A woman and a boy were 
taken to Los Angeles County-USC Medical Center but their conditions 
were not immediately known. 
</P>
<P>
	Rivera's ex-girlfriend and her current boyfriend were visiting  
the current boyfriend's relatives when Rivera showed up, Stuart 
said. 
</P>
<P>
	``The suspect ... walked inside and began shooting just pretty  
much randomly,'' Stuart said. 
</P>
<P>
	Rivera and the woman had two children together but broke up two  
years ago, Stuart said. It was unclear if the children were among 
the victims. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
